"a.幸运的；恰到好处的 无 adj. 幸运的; 由神的干预才发生的 【记】pro前, vid看, ential: 总是向前看, 不容易失败－幸运的 【反】unfortunate(adj 不幸的); mishap(n 灾祸) 【记】provident 为将来考虑，原指神的意旨，神掌控一切，考虑未来，能带来好运的 providential (adj.)  1610s, ""pertaining to foresifght"" (implied in providentially); 1640s as ""pertaining to divine providence,"" from Latin providentia (see providence) + -al (1). Meaning ""by divine interposition"" is recorded from 1719."
